# Preserve every file's line endings verbatim — do NOT normalize.
#
# The repository baseline is mixed: most text files are LF, a handful are CRLF.
# A prior `* text=auto` rewrote every CRLF blob to LF on commit, which made
# those unchanged files render as fully modified (no-op, line-ending-only diffs)
# in pull requests. `-text` disables end-of-line conversion for all files
# regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting, so each file keeps its
# existing endings on add and checkout and nothing is silently flipped. Diff and
# merge still treat these as text (unlike `binary`).
* -text

# Images: no line-ending conversion, and no diff/merge either.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
